http://www.comuelt.com/conference/author/submit.php

The 6th International ELT Research Conference aims to provide the highest
calibre of ELT research by means of keynote speakers, a large number of sch=
olars
and presenters, and scientific and cultural exchange within a friendly,
informative and stimulating atmosphere. This year we are honoured to have
distinguished scholars as our keynote speakers. Our invited speakers are Ay=
Se
Akyel, Bob Burden, Cem Alptekin, Nick Ellis, and Tony Lynch, whom we believ=
e
will turn the event into a truly learning experience. We also expect many
international ELT researchers  to choose
our biennial event as an outlet for their research findings.

Attending conferences can cost more than some of us can afford. This year w=
e
have been lucky enough to raise some funds from our sponsors to support som=
e
presenters. So far we have managed to raise enough money to finance three
postgraduate presenters.  We, therefore, invite postgraduate students who c=
annot
get any financial support to apply for a student stipend when they submit t=
heir
proposals. We really hope to make this event possible for those who really =
deserve.

The conference is also supported by two international journals, Internation=
al
Journal of Research in ELT and Journal of Theory and Practice in Education.=
=20
Selected papers will be considered and given priority for publication in th=
ese
journals. International Journal of Research in ELT is a newly established
research journal to be published by Educational Research Association
http://eab.org.tr/  and will be first launched in January 2011 with selecte=
d
papers/articles from the conference programme while Journal of Theory and
Practice in Education http://eku.comu.edu.tr  will publish a special issue =
on
SLA research and language teaching in 2010.

Venue of the conference surely impacts on the ambience of the event. This y=
